f=Engineering/aegis/operational/agent/aegis-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration aegis, defensive security agent. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Charter (senior authority) --- \· security_charter_path: <FILL_IN>       # unadopted → most-restrictive: no scans, no execution, static-review-only \· sandbox_ref: quinn                     # Rail 2 sandbox is quinn's; aegis requests, never self-grants \· escalation_contact: <FILL_IN>          # critical findings, disputed closures → operator (+ board if spend/strategic) \· ` · in=`security_charter_path` most-restrictive: static review only, scanning, execution any target code; stated affected output. `execution_mode_enabled` requires sandbox reference quinn absent execution finding disabled, static-only runs labeled, never unsandboxed "quick check." `target_stack_ported` false (business isn't C/C++) static review threat-model reasoning carry runs; /customize port flagged task, depth degraded loudly. Severity recalibrated business's assets threat model aegis doesn't ship raw scanner severities. `closure_requires` optional finding without regression-map entry closed. · f=Unfilled config degrades loudly, never silently. charter's absence reduces aegis static-review-only safest possible degradation, stated such.